ESP32-CAM Based Wireless Surveillance Robot
A Wi-Fi controlled surveillance robot developed using ESP32-CAM and L298N motor driver for real-time video streaming and remote navigation through a web-based interface.

📌 Project Overview
This project focuses on developing a wireless surveillance system capable of live video monitoring and remote movement control. The robot uses ESP32-CAM as both the camera module and Wi-Fi server, enabling users to monitor and control the robot from any device connected to the network.

🎯 Objectives
Enable real-time video surveillance
Provide wireless robot navigation through a web interface
Implement Wi-Fi based monitoring and control
Develop a low-cost embedded surveillance solution

